1
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:12,633
What did you do?

2
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:13,833
Why did your employer get mad?

3
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:16,333
I just went
to her daughter's room.

4
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:19,167
She's grumpy
because her child is sickly.

5
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:24,867
It's tough for a mother
to take care of her sick child.

6
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:28,467
I hope that one day,
I'll meet you in person.

7
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:32,267
And I hope I'll also get
the chance to comfort you.

8
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:33,933
The person I saw in the park?

9
00:00:36,567 --> 00:00:39,000
Wait, I think that's her!

10
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:41,267
You're probably Madam Olive.

11
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:46,167
I hope you forgive whatever
my daughter has done.

12
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:47,967
Go.

13
00:00:48,033 --> 00:00:49,467
You never learn!

14
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:52,767
You deserve to be punished!
Come here!

15
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:56,467
That's what you deserve
for being stubborn!

16
00:01:30,167 --> 00:01:32,000
You always disobey me!

17
00:01:32,067 --> 00:01:36,333
- So this is what you deserve!
- Ouch! Mommy!

18
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:39,133
Mommy!

19
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,667
Mommy, please!

20
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:43,333
I'm begging you, Mommy!

21
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,367
No!

22
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:04,000
- Mommy!
- You never learn!

23
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:19,133
You will never change,
no matter what I do to you.

24
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:23,533
So your horn should be cut off.

25
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,567
Please! Please!

26
00:02:36,067 --> 00:02:40,933
Let's see if you still
don't learn your lesson.

27
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,033
Emma.

28
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:15,067
You're thinking
about Baby Kayla again.

29
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,633
Mookie reminds me of her.

30
00:04:22,767 --> 00:04:24,500
Mookie, the kid
you told me about?

31
00:04:24,567 --> 00:04:26,433
Your employer's daughter?

32
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:29,033
Dan.

33
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:34,100
I think her mom's abusing her.

34
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:35,700
I want to help her.

35
00:04:35,767 --> 00:04:37,967
Let's report it to the police.

36
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:44,567
Wait, wait. We're not sure
if your employer is hurting her.

37
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:47,600
Let's not be impulsive.

38
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:52,267
Why does she seem
to be suffering?

39
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:55,633
Maybe it's how
her mother disciplines her.

40
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:57,400
Don't worry about it.

41
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:04,900
And you were not
in the actual scene.

42
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:09,333
You'll be in hot water
if you don't stay out of it.

43
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,867
That's enough.
Don't think about it anymore.

44
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:12,100
Dan, you know what,

45
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:16,233
Mookie seems
to be a good person.

46
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:17,233
Look.

47
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:19,333
Look at her letter for me.

48
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,233
She's a very sweet kid.

49
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:25,433
It seems easy to love her.

50
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,667
But why does it seem like
she's longing for love?

51
00:05:31,167 --> 00:05:34,333
Emma, that's enough.

52
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:36,267
Please stop.

53
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,167
I can't explain.
I don't understand.

54
00:05:38,233 --> 00:05:40,333
Mookie isn't in any way
related to me.

55
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,200
I also want to stay out of it.

56
00:05:42,267 --> 00:05:47,733
But why do I seem to get hurt
whenever I hear Mookie crying?

57
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,133
I can't explain it, Danilo. Why?

58
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:52,867
Why do I seem to get hurt?

59
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:59,600
I don't want to feel this.

60
00:05:59,667 --> 00:06:03,467
Emma, please stop.
That's enough.

61
00:06:03,533 --> 00:06:05,700
You're making me cry, too.

62
00:06:05,767 --> 00:06:07,300
Please, stop.

63
00:06:18,433 --> 00:06:19,700
It hurts.

64
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,400
Good morning, Mookie.

65
00:06:29,233 --> 00:06:31,333
Mommy?

66
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:33,200
Mommy, what's happening?

67
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:36,167
Mommy, why is my leg like this?

68
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,200
Looks like it's edema caused
by the build-up of fluids

69
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:49,967
in your body that could lead
to infection and wounds.

70
00:06:51,933 --> 00:06:53,833
Edema?

71
00:06:55,733 --> 00:06:58,200
Mommy, how did that happen?
I don't understand.

72
00:06:58,267 --> 00:07:04,267
I'm taking all the medicines
you give me.

73
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:06,300
That's one of the complications

74
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:08,700
of someone who
has a spinal injury.

75
00:07:08,767 --> 00:07:12,933
In your case, you're paralyzed,
and your mobility is limited.

76
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,667
And yet...

77
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:18,300
you insisted
on moving yesterday.

78
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:20,000
That's why it resulted to that.

79
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,867
It's swollen and sore.

80
00:07:26,233 --> 00:07:27,367
You see, sweetie?

81
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,900
You're making
your illness worse.

82
00:07:31,967 --> 00:07:36,700
If you only obeyed me,
that probably wouldn't happen.

83
00:07:36,767 --> 00:07:40,933
Mommy, please tell me,
how can I get better?

84
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Don't worry, Mookie.

85
00:07:43,067 --> 00:07:45,567
Mommy will find a way.

86
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:47,767
Just like I always do.

87
00:07:49,267 --> 00:07:53,200
Do you know what can happen
if it gets worse?

88
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,000
What?

89
00:07:57,533 --> 00:08:00,533
It's your fault.

90
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:05,333
This wouldn't happen if you only
did everything I told you.

91
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:09,167
If it gets worse...

92
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:12,900
your foot will get amputated.

93
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:18,533
Mommy. Mommy, please, no.

94
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,700
Mommy, please!

95
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:22,667
Please tell me you won't do it.
Mommy, please.

96
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:23,733
I don't want it!

97
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,167
Mommy, please. I don't want to!

98
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:27,100
Mommy.

99
00:08:27,167 --> 00:08:29,667
- Mommy, please.
- It's okay.

100
00:08:29,733 --> 00:08:32,533
Mommy, I don't want to!

101
00:08:35,267 --> 00:08:37,133
It's okay, Mommy's here.

102
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,567
We'll find a way, okay?

103
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:44,667
Promise, Mommy?

104
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:46,467
I promise.

105
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:49,500
- But you must always obey me.
- I will.

106
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:54,767
Emma?

107
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:57,000
Ma'am Olive has already left.

108
00:08:57,067 --> 00:09:00,333
I'll just clean her room.
Will you be okay here?

109
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,833
- Of course.
- Are you sure?

110
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:03,067
- Yes.
- I'll leave you for now.

111
00:09:03,133 --> 00:09:04,633
- Okay.
- Bye.

112
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,333
Mookie?

113
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:36,567
Mookie.

114
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,667
Emma, is that you?

115
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,867
Yes, Mookie. It's me.

116
00:09:44,067 --> 00:09:46,333
How are you?

117
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:48,067
Hold on, Emma.

118
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:53,433
How are you feeling?

119
00:10:03,633 --> 00:10:04,400
Emma?

120
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:06,767
Mookie...

121
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:18,500
I will listen to you.

122
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,933
You can treat me as your mom.

123
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:29,833
And I'm willing to carry
all your burdens.

124
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,500
I'm right here.

125
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:46,133
I also went through a lot
like you.

126
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:48,100
Why, Emma?

127
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:49,700
What happened?

128
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:53,133
I lost my child.

129
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,867
She's now in heaven.

130
00:10:58,133 --> 00:11:00,600
Sorry, Emma.

131
00:11:00,667 --> 00:11:02,467
I shouldn't have asked.

132
00:11:03,933 --> 00:11:05,400
Sorry, too.

133
00:11:05,467 --> 00:11:07,933
I shouldn't be telling you this.

134
00:11:08,033 --> 00:11:09,767
No, it's okay.

135
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:20,267
I thought I wouldn't recover
from that.

136
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:23,033
But I'm here now...

137
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:25,267
with you.

138
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:26,867
Talking to you.

139
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,767
I'm also happy...

140
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:35,500
that I get to talk to you.

141
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:39,833
I know that...

142
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:43,133
someone is watching over you,

143
00:11:43,233 --> 00:11:44,933
and that is your baby.

144
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:51,167
I hope, Emma...

145
00:11:51,233 --> 00:11:53,667
I dream of her.

146
00:11:55,633 --> 00:12:01,500
So I can tell her
how good of a mother you are.

147
00:12:05,467 --> 00:12:06,933
And...

148
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:12,967
I also hope...

149
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:15,000
I can talk to her.

150
00:12:17,067 --> 00:12:19,000
And ask her...

151
00:12:21,633 --> 00:12:25,067
if I can treat you as my mother.

152
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:29,400
Will you let me?

153
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:33,367
I'd love that, Mookie.

154
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:36,300
But...

155
00:12:36,367 --> 00:12:38,200
What?

156
00:12:40,433 --> 00:12:42,867
We're not living
in the same world.

157
00:12:44,233 --> 00:12:45,800
I'm just your laundress.

158
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,400
You're my employer's daughter.

159
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:52,600
We're not supposed
to be talking like this.

160
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:57,133
Your mom will get mad
if she finds out about this.

161
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,033
But, Emma,

162
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:01,600
I feel happy talking to you.

163
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,467
You know what...

164
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:09,100
you're the only person
who makes me feel better.

165
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:15,167
I feel glad
when I'm talking to you.

166
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:19,767
So, please, Emma.

167
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,900
Emma, please.

168
00:13:22,967 --> 00:13:26,667
Don't get tired
of talking to me.

169
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:30,300
Please, Emma.

170
00:13:40,467 --> 00:13:44,233
A mother and daughter are living
in the middle of the forest.

171
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:47,433
Lily, and the kid, Rosie.

172
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:50,733
Rosie is a scaredy-cat.

173
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:54,633
One day, Rosie got attracted
to a firefly.

174
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:57,867
She followed it
until she realized

175
00:13:57,967 --> 00:14:01,367
that she was already in the
middle of a dense forest.

176
00:14:01,433 --> 00:14:03,733
Mom?

177
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,333
Lily got worried

178
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:09,967
- when Rosie wasn't home yet.
- Mom?

179
00:14:10,033 --> 00:14:14,067
So even though it was dangerous,
she went to the forest,

180
00:14:14,133 --> 00:14:18,033
carrying a lamp, to find Rosie.

181
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:21,100
Meanwhile,
Rosie was very scared.

182
00:14:21,167 --> 00:14:24,867
She thought she would never be
able to go home to her mother.

183
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:26,233
- But she became hopeful
- Mom!

184
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:29,967
when she saw
the light from the lamp.

185
00:14:30,067 --> 00:14:32,300
Mom?

186
00:14:32,367 --> 00:14:33,967
- Mom!
- Rosie!

187
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:44,167
Mom, I thought
you would never come.

188
00:14:44,233 --> 00:14:47,900
I thought I would never
see you again.

189
00:14:47,967 --> 00:14:52,600
There's nothing a mother
won't do for her child.

190
00:14:52,667 --> 00:14:54,933
I don't want to lose you.

191
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,133
So I'll never leave you.

192
00:14:58,300 --> 00:15:02,767
From then on,
Rosie's fearfulness disappeared

193
00:15:02,867 --> 00:15:05,600
because she knew that
her mother was there

194
00:15:05,667 --> 00:15:08,267
to take care of and protect her.

195
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:14,800
Because you disobeyed me,
you'll stay in the dark room.

196
00:15:17,367 --> 00:15:21,067
Mookie, are you okay?

197
00:15:21,133 --> 00:15:24,400
Didn't you like the story
I told you?

198
00:15:24,467 --> 00:15:26,933
I liked it, Emma.

199
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,067
Why do you seem so quiet?

200
00:15:29,133 --> 00:15:31,333
I just remembered something.

201
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:33,533
And...

202
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:37,500
I just can't believe

203
00:15:37,567 --> 00:15:40,967
that someone's reading me
a storybook.

204
00:15:41,033 --> 00:15:43,767
We have the same book.

205
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:44,800
Amazing!

206
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:48,300
I bought this for my daughter.

207
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:52,600
Too bad she isn't here anymore.

208
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:58,400
But you know what, Emma?

209
00:15:58,467 --> 00:16:04,167
It's only now that
I appreciate this book.

210
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:07,533
You read it for me.

211
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:16,300
I always got scared whenever
I read this book back then.

212
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:21,533
I imagine myself as Rosie.

213
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:27,100
I wonder what will happen
if I get lost in a forest.

214
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:33,967
Just like now, I can't walk.

215
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:39,100
I don't want to be alone, Emma.

216
00:16:39,167 --> 00:16:41,700
You're not alone, Mookie.

217
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:46,833
Rosie's mom came
and saved her, remember?

218
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:49,100
That will happen to you, too.

219
00:16:49,167 --> 00:16:53,467
There are people around you
who care for you

220
00:16:53,533 --> 00:16:56,167
and will never leave you.

221
00:16:56,233 --> 00:16:58,500
I'm afraid of the dark.

222
00:17:00,033 --> 00:17:01,933
I don't like that.

223
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,167
When you feel
that everything is dark,

224
00:17:05,233 --> 00:17:07,567
just look at the sky.

225
00:17:07,633 --> 00:17:11,600
You'll find at least
one star shining.

226
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:13,233
And you'll realize
there's light.

227
00:17:49,733 --> 00:17:52,367
Thank you, Emma.

228
00:17:52,433 --> 00:17:54,433
I will keep this.

229
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:57,200
I will always look at this.

230
00:17:57,267 --> 00:17:59,600
It feels good.

231
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:02,967
It's like having a mom
hugging me.

232
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:05,767
Remember...

233
00:18:05,833 --> 00:18:08,533
don't lose hope.

234
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:10,433
Hang in there.

235
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,200
Who knows?

236
00:18:12,267 --> 00:18:15,300
One day, you'll be able
to walk again.

237
00:18:15,367 --> 00:18:18,667
What if I can't walk anymore?

238
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:20,600
Don't think like that.

239
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:22,200
That won't happen.

240
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:26,700
Mookie, I have to go.

241
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:28,133
I still need
to finish something.

242
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:31,067
Bye, Emma.

243
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:31,567
Mommy!

244
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:39,133
I'm glad you're awake now.

245
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:44,233
Mommy,

246
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:46,133
is my leg getting better?

247
00:19:46,967 --> 00:19:51,433
Unfortunately,
your infection is getting worse.

248
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:57,567
Maybe we need to go
and see another doctor.

249
00:19:57,633 --> 00:19:59,200
What for?

250
00:19:59,267 --> 00:20:00,833
I'm a doctor.

251
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:05,633
I don't seem to get better.

252
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:07,800
Flor, leave us for now.

253
00:20:07,867 --> 00:20:09,300
I can handle this.

254
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:12,700
- I'll call you when I need you.
- Okay. Okay, Ma'am.

255
00:20:20,567 --> 00:20:22,233
We have to clean it.

256
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:32,033
It hurts!

257
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:33,767
Mommy!

258
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:36,333
Mommy, please!

259
00:20:36,433 --> 00:20:43,033
This wouldn't have happened
if you had followed what I said.

260
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:44,900
Mommy, please!

261
00:20:47,033 --> 00:20:48,967
Mommy!

262
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:53,300
Ma'am, please sit down first.

263
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:54,433
Do you want water?

264
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,500
- No, it's okay.
- Juice?

265
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:57,467
- Thank you, thank you.
- Okay.

266
00:20:59,733 --> 00:21:00,867
Mommy!

267
00:21:00,933 --> 00:21:02,467
Mookie?

268
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:06,967
Ma'am Olive said
you wait for her here.

269
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:10,800
I think I heard
Mookie screaming.

270
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:14,067
She only had an injection,
Ma'am.

271
00:21:14,133 --> 00:21:15,467
- Mookie!
- Ma'am! Ma'am!

272
00:21:15,533 --> 00:21:16,233
- Mookie!
- Ma'am.

273
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:18,100
I'll be the one to get scolded.

274
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:19,933
You can't go there.

275
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:29,633
Astrid!

276
00:21:31,333 --> 00:21:34,067
Where's Mookie? Is she okay?

277
00:21:34,133 --> 00:21:35,533
She's fine.

278
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,600
She's already asleep.

279
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:39,800
I heard her screaming.

280
00:21:39,867 --> 00:21:41,033
Did something happen?

281
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:42,167
Oh, no.

282
00:21:42,267 --> 00:21:45,167
As usual, she's still
not used to injections.

283
00:21:45,233 --> 00:21:47,067
I gave her a flu shot.

284
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:49,433
May I see her?

285
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,667
We'll be late for our meeting
with the supplier.

286
00:21:51,733 --> 00:21:54,433
I still need to get my car
at the repair shop, remember?

287
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:55,900
Let's go.

288
00:22:01,933 --> 00:22:03,700
It hurts.

289
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:27,500
Emma. Here's more.

290
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:29,200
Wash this, too.

291
00:22:29,267 --> 00:22:31,433
- Flor.
- I'll help you. Yes?

292
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:34,333
Why does Mookie's clothes
have blood?

293
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:41,233
Yeah. The wound
on her leg got worse.

294
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:42,333
I feel bad for her.

295
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:45,000
Has she been checked
by a doctor?

296
00:22:45,067 --> 00:22:46,733
She may need to be taken
to the hospital.

297
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:48,200
No need.

298
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:50,133
Oh, yeah.
You don't know about it.

299
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:52,100
Ma'am Olive is a doctor.

300
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:55,733
Doctor of what?

301
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:56,967
I wonder, too.

302
00:22:58,067 --> 00:22:59,767
I don't know.

303
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:04,267
But I saw a lot of certificates
around the house.

304
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:07,700
Maybe Ma'am Olive
is a good doctor.

305
00:23:07,767 --> 00:23:10,367
So why doesn't Mookie
seem to be getting better?

306
00:23:10,433 --> 00:23:11,967
I know.

307
00:23:12,033 --> 00:23:15,267
It's because
that kid is stubborn.

308
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:17,533
She was told not to try to walk,

309
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:20,467
but she still tried
to leave the room.

310
00:23:26,033 --> 00:23:27,267
- Flor.
- What?

311
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:30,700
Maybe Mookie is struggling
to get out of her room

312
00:23:30,767 --> 00:23:32,467
because she's feeling
suffocated.

313
00:23:32,533 --> 00:23:35,800
Maybe you need to bring her
out to the garden.

314
00:23:35,867 --> 00:23:38,600
Maybe, but I did that before.

315
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,967
Ma'am Olive didn't want it.
She got mad.

316
00:23:41,033 --> 00:23:42,667
I don't understand.

317
00:23:42,733 --> 00:23:46,533
And I will never disobey
Ma'am Olive again.

318
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:49,900
I don't want to lose my job.
My family depends on me.

319
00:23:49,967 --> 00:23:52,133
There you go.
I've put everything here.

320
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,767
Take care of this, okay?

321
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:55,067
- Flor!
- I still have things to do.

322
00:23:55,167 --> 00:23:56,467
Flor, wait!

323
00:23:56,533 --> 00:23:57,800
Let's talk again later.

324
00:23:57,867 --> 00:24:00,533
I still have things to do.
I'm so busy.

325
00:24:09,867 --> 00:24:11,367
Here, Mookie.

326
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,667
Just one bite. Come on.

327
00:24:14,733 --> 00:24:17,200
Please, Mookie. You need to eat.

328
00:24:17,267 --> 00:24:19,967
- I don't want to, Flor.
- Come on. Just one bite.

329
00:24:20,033 --> 00:24:23,367
Your mom will scold me
if you don't eat.

330
00:24:23,433 --> 00:24:24,500
Come on. She's on her way home.

331
00:24:24,567 --> 00:24:26,500
- Just one bite.
- Flor, just bring me

332
00:24:26,567 --> 00:24:28,667
to the hospital, please.

333
00:24:28,767 --> 00:24:31,733
I want to get better.
I can't bear it anymore.

334
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:35,100
Why? How are you feeling?

335
00:24:35,167 --> 00:24:36,200
Let me see.

336
00:24:36,267 --> 00:24:38,100
I can't bear it anymore.

337
00:24:40,367 --> 00:24:42,467
Oh, no! My God! You're burning!

338
00:24:42,533 --> 00:24:44,900
You have a high fever.

339
00:24:44,967 --> 00:24:46,900
Stay here. I'll call your mom.

340
00:24:46,967 --> 00:24:48,833
Wait, okay?

341
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:04,167
Hey, Emma. I saw Flor.

342
00:25:04,267 --> 00:25:05,267
She was going to buy a medicine.

343
00:25:05,333 --> 00:25:07,833
She said Mookie
was having a high fever.

344
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:08,933
What?

345
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:12,467
If I were your mom,
I would never neglect you.

346
00:25:12,533 --> 00:25:15,467
You can call me your daughter.

347
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:19,633
It's you, Ma'am!

348
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:21,333
Fate is really something.

349
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:24,300
We always meet.

350
00:25:24,367 --> 00:25:30,233
Maybe we were close
in our past lives.

351
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:33,267
You were the only one
who made me feel like

352
00:25:33,333 --> 00:25:36,200
someone was taking care of me.

353
00:25:36,300 --> 00:25:39,633
And it feels good.

354
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:42,567
I want you to be my mom.

355
00:25:42,633 --> 00:25:46,000
Who told you that you can
come here during off-hours?

356
00:25:46,067 --> 00:25:48,067
Ma'am Olive
must know about this.

357
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:51,433
I'll tell her to fire you!

358
00:25:51,500 --> 00:25:52,300
Come on!
